<section class="page-section story-open">
  <div class="page-section__inner">
    {%- if section.settings.lede != blank -%}
      <p class="story-open__lede">{{ section.settings.lede }}</p>
    {%- endif -%}

    <div class="story-open__flow">
      {%- for block in section.blocks -%}
        <article class="story-passage" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
          {%- if block.settings.eyebrow != blank -%}
            <span class="eyebrow">{{ block.settings.eyebrow }}</span>
          {%- endif -%}
          {%- if block.settings.heading != blank -%}
            <h2 class="story-passage__h display-h">{{ block.settings.heading }}</h2>
          {%- endif -%}
          <div class="story-passage__body">{{ block.settings.body }}</div>
        </article>
      {%- endfor -%}
    </div>

    <figure class="story-open__photo">
      {%- if section.settings.image != blank -%}
        {{ section.settings.image | image_url: width: 1600 | image_tag: loading: 'lazy', widths: '800,1200,1600', alt: section.settings.caption }}
      {%- else -%}
        <div class="story-open__photo-ph" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      {%- endif -%}
      <figcaption class="story-open__caption">{{ section.settings.caption }}</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div>
</section>

{% stylesheet %}
.story-open { background: var(--c-cream); }
.story-open__lede { max-width: 24ch; margin: 0 0 clamp(48px, 7vw, 88px); font-family: var(--ff-display); font-size: clamp(30px, 4.4vw, 56px); line-height: 1.18; color: var(--c-forest); font-weight: 500; }
.story-open__flow { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: clamp(36px, 5vw, 72px) clamp(40px, 6vw, 96px); }
.story-passage__h { font-size: clamp(24px, 2.6vw, 34px); margin: 14px 0 0; }
.story-passage .eyebrow { display: inline-block; }
.story-passage__body { margin: 16px 0 0; max-width: 52ch; color: var(--c-ink-soft); line-height: 1.8; }
.story-passage__body p { margin: 0 0 14px; }
.story-passage__body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
.story-open__photo { margin: clamp(56px, 8vw, 104px) 0 0; }
.story-open__photo img, .story-open__photo-ph { display: block; width: 100%; border-radius: 16px; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9; object-fit: contain; }
.story-open__photo-ph { background: var(--grad-sage); box-shadow: inset 0 0 120px rgba(14,33,24,.35); }
.story-open__caption { margin: 16px 0 0; font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: .1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--c-ink-mute); text-align: center; }
@media (max-width: 70px) { .story-open__flow { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
{% endstylesheet %}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Story Opening",
  "settings": [
    { "type": "textarea", "id": "lede", "label": "Lede paragraph", "default": "Some houses begin with an idea. Ours began with a request — and a pharmacist who could not say no." },
    { "type": "image_picker", "id": "image", "label": "Founder photo (optional)" },
    { "type": "text", "id": "caption", "label": "Photo caption", "default": "The founding pharmacists, in the compounding lab — Houston." }
  ],
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "passage",
      "name": "Passage",
      "settings": [
        { "type": "text", "id": "eyebrow", "label": "Eyebrow", "default": "— The origin —" },
        { "type": "text", "id": "heading", "label": "Heading", "default": "A bench in Houston" },
        { "type": "richtext", "id": "body", "label": "Body", "default": "<p>It began on a compounding bench in Houston, where two pharmacists spent their days weighing actives by the milligram for patients.</p>" }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "Story Opening",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "passage",
          "settings": {
            "eyebrow": "— The origin —",
            "heading": "A bench in Houston",
            "body": "<p>It began on a compounding bench in Houston, where two pharmacists spent their days weighing actives to the milligram. The frustration was quiet at first: the retinol a wife tried burned her cheeks, the vitamin C a mother bought oxidised brown within a week. So the founders did what pharmacists do — they compounded a better one by hand, on the bench, until it was right.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "passage",
          "settings": {
            "eyebrow": "— Why they built it —",
            "heading": "For the women they love",
            "body": "<p>Chemistrie was never made for a market. The first formulas were made for the women the founders came home to — wives, mothers, daughters — the people whose faces they knew well enough to formulate for. A serum only left the bench once one of them would keep using it. That is still the test.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "passage",
          "settings": {
            "eyebrow": "— The promise —",
            "heading": "Honest to the milligram",
            "body": "<p>Every batch is compounded by hand in runs capped at 200 bottles, then hand-numbered before it ships, so nothing sits waiting on a shelf while its actives fade. Each concentration is printed exactly as compounded — no rounding, no marketing blends.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "passage",
          "settings": {
            "eyebrow": "— The promise, kept —",
            "heading": "A pharmacist still answers",
            "body": "<p>Write to Chemistrie and a pharmacist answers — the same person who might have weighed the actives in your bottle. The house has grown, but the bench has not moved, and neither has the standard: make it work, make it kind, make it worthy of the person who will use it nightly.</p>"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
